sword ban in this country?

78
00:05:16,650 --> 00:05:17,784
That's against the law!

79
00:05:17,784 --> 00:05:19,119
You're getting a fine, buddy.

80
00:05:19,119 --> 00:05:20,954
That'll be a million, minimum.

81
00:05:20,954 --> 00:05:23,557
Since there's three of us,
that's three million.

82
00:05:24,991 --> 00:05:26,693
What a filthy stick!

83
00:05:27,527 --> 00:05:29,629
It kinda smells like curry,
doesn't it?

84
00:05:29,763 --> 00:05:32,465
So, you're asking me
to buy this from you?

85
00:05:32,732 --> 00:05:34,801
I want to buy stuff from
the Shopping Channel.

86
00:05:35,235 --> 00:05:36,870
I don't really understand
your circumstances,

87
00:05:36,870 --> 00:05:38,572
but I can't pay you for this.

88
00:05:38,705 --> 00:05:41,408
However, I'd buy that odd creature
over there, if you want.

89
00:05:42,676 --> 00:05:43,677
Damn you.

90
00:05:43,810 --> 00:05:45,879
Don't you realize that
we're Government officials?

91
00:05:47,847 --> 00:05:50,317
Phew! This thing totally
reeks of curry!

92
00:05:50,317 --> 00:05:52,719
And it says "Lake Toya",
isn't this a souvenir?

93
00:05:53,153 --> 00:05:54,521
I don't want it.

94
00:05:59,926 --> 00:06:01,628
‐Stop right there!
‐Hey, you stop!

95
00:06:01,628 --> 00:06:02,829
Where's the sword.

96
00:06:03,029 --> 00:06:04,197
The legendary sword...?

97
00:06:04,197 --> 00:06:08,668
You know, I really can't stand
Earth foods at all especially curry.

98
00:06:17,611 --> 00:06:18,612
What?

99
00:06:18,745 --> 00:06:19,446
A wooden sword?

100
00:06:19,446 --> 00:06:21,548
If it belonged to a handsome guy,
perhaps I'll buy it.

101
00:06:21,548 --> 00:06:23,049
I'll give you a really good price...

102
00:06:23,049 --> 00:06:25,886
but I have no interest in something
of yours, young lady.

103
00:06:26,019 --> 00:06:27,220
Come on!

104
00:06:27,420 --> 00:06:29,256
Why won't anyone buy
this stick from me?!

105
00:06:29,256 --> 00:06:30,757
You useless stick!

106
00:06:30,957 --> 00:06:32,626
I don't even get paid properly,

107
00:06:32,626 --> 00:06:35,462
so how am I supposed to buy
the things I want, huh?

108
00:06:35,629 --> 00:06:37,697
Last month, I got paid
in pickled seaweed!

109
00:06:37,697 --> 00:06:39,799
How sour can a
person's wage get?

110
00:06:41,101 --> 00:06:42,669
‐H‐Hey!
‐The bridge!

111
00:06:42,802 --> 00:06:44,504
Is my teenage life going
to be filled

112
00:06:44,504 --> 00:06:46,940
with nothing but memories
of pickled seaweed?

113
00:06:50,610 --> 00:06:52,646
This isn't it, or this either.

114
00:06:53,747 --> 00:06:55,882
A monster on the bridge!

115
00:06:56,182 --> 00:06:58,618
What is that wooden sword?!
The bridge is gone!

116
00:06:59,219 --> 00:07:00,587
Wooden sword?

117
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:08,762
I can't even go home
even if I wanted to.

118
00:07:08,762 --> 00:07:11,731
Because I took his precious
sword without his permission.

119
00:07:11,898 --> 00:07:14,367
Gin's probably fuming
right about now.

120
00:07:22,909 --> 00:07:24,377
Who the hell are you?

121
00:07:24,711 --> 00:07:25,879
Little girl.

122
00:07:26,146 --> 00:07:28,315
Where did you get that
wooden sword there?

123
00:07:29,182 --> 00:07:30,917
The way that it cut a bridge
clean in two.

124
00:07:30,917 --> 00:07:32,919
I've found it at last...

125
00:07:33,186 --> 00:07:35,155
the legendary Star Destroyer!

126
00:07:35,555 --> 00:07:39,392
Hand me that sword right now,
and I shall spare your life little girl.

127
00:07:47,767 --> 00:07:49,803
Now you've done it, little girl!

128
00:08:03,049 --> 00:08:04,117
A "Sword Hunter"?

129
00:08:04,117 --> 00:08:05,185
Yeah, that's right.

130
00:08:05,185 --> 00:08:07,587
There seems to be a lot of
attacks around town.

131
00:08:07,587 --> 00:08:09,522
The hunter is apparently
an Amanto...

132
00:08:09,522 --> 00:08:11,324
training to become
the strongest warrior

133
00:08:11,324 --> 00:08:13,360
in the universe or
something like that.

134
00:08:19,866 --> 00:08:21,901
He's apparently really strong, too.

135
00:08:21,901 --> 00:08:23,837
Seems many Government
retainers and mercenaries

136
00:08:23,837 --> 00:08:25,905
have already fallen to his strength.

137
00:08:26,206 --> 00:08:28,375
That might have been his work
we just saw back there?

138
00:08:28,375 --> 00:08:30,243
The strongest in the universe, huh?

139
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:32,245
I don't know what sort of
dream he's chasing,

140
00:08:32,245 --> 00:08:33,680
but the stupidity of men stays

141
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:35,548
the same no matter
what star you're from.

142
00:08:35,749 --> 00:08:37,851
All of these guys spend too much
time reading comics.

143
00:08:38,051 --> 00:08:40,787
He might come after your
wooden sword, too, Gin.

144
00:08:40,787 --> 00:08:42,522
<i>That</i> <i>wooden</i> <i>sword</i> <i>is</i>
<i>much</i> <i>more</i> <i>powerful</i>

145
00:08:42,522 --> 00:08:44,391
<i>than</i> <i>an</i> <i>ordinary</i>
<i>metal</i> <i>one</i> <i>after</i> <i>all.</i>

146
00:08:44,591 --> 00:08:45,892
<i>It cuts through everything.</i>

147
00:08:46,192 --> 00:08:48,328
Why on earth is that
thing so strong?

148
00:08:48,328 --> 00:08:49,863
The thing about that thing is, well.

149
00:08:50,130 --> 00:08:52,198
When I was on a school field
trip to Lake Toya Resort,

150
00:08:52,198 --> 00:08:53,700
there was a hermit who lived there.

151
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:54,501
Hold on.

152
00:08:54,501 --> 00:08:56,436
Now that you mention it,
what'd I do with it?

153
00:09:02,675 --> 00:09:04,477
What's with that guy, Sadaharu?

154
00:09:04,644 --> 00:09:07,580
We should hide here for a while,
don't you think Sada.

155
00:09:09,883 --> 00:09:11,284
I found you, little girl.

156
00:09:11,284 --> 00:09:13,520
Hey, what the hell is
your problem, huh?

157
00:09:13,653 --> 00:09:14,454
And you, too!

158
00:09:14,454 --> 00:09:15,922
Pay up, girl!

159
00:09:15,922 --> 00:09:17,490
That guy will pay for me!

160
00:09:17,891 --> 00:09:19,325
You're not getting away!

161
00:09:19,559 --> 00:09:21,294
I've seen many swords up until now,

162
00:09:21,294 --> 00:09:23,830
but your sword is the legendary
sword I have been searching

163
00:09:23,830 --> 00:09:26,232
for all these years,
The Star Destroyer!

164
00:09:31,504 --> 00:09:34,074
Don't get so excited,
you sword freak.

165
00:09:36,242 --> 00:09:38,311
It seems like you
underestimated me.

166
00:09:38,445 --> 00:09:40,980
You held back so as to not kill me
didn't you, little girl?

167
00:09:42,248 --> 00:09:43,783
But we of the Genbu Clan...

168
00:09:43,783 --> 00:09:47,454
have hardened bodies that
even bullets bounce off of.

169
00:09:47,454 --> 00:09:49,956
With this body and the
Star Destroyer Sword,

170
00:09:49,956 --> 00:09:51,658
no one can stand against me!

171
00:09:52,158 --> 00:09:53,560
The strongest sword
should be wielded

172
00:09:53,560 --> 00:09:55,695
by the strongest warrior
in the universe!

173
00:09:55,829 --> 00:09:56,563
Now!

174
00:09:56,729 --> 00:09:58,865
Accept your defeat
and hand it over.

175
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:02,268
<i>Oh, this must be my punishment...</i>

176
00:10:02,435 --> 00:10:05,705
<i>for bad karma because I stole</i>
<i>someone's cherished possession.</i>

177
00:10:05,705 --> 00:10:08,174
<i>So now, God is trying</i>
<i>to set me straight.</i>

178
00:10:08,541 --> 00:10:10,310
<i>But please listen to me, God.</i>

179
00:10:10,310 --> 00:10:13,413
<i>Gintoki doesn't even</i>
<i>pay me a real salary.</i>

180
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:14,581
<i>And even worse...</i>

181
00:10:14,581 --> 00:10:17,317
<i>he took away everything</i>
<i>that I cherished.</i>

182
00:10:18,685 --> 00:10:22,922
<i>Maybe I should hand over his wooden</i>
<i>sword and make it easy on myself.</i>

183
00:10:23,356 --> 00:10:24,290
<i>No, wait.</i>

184
00:10:24,290 --> 00:10:27,193
<i>If I did that, then I would</i>
<i>be exactly like him.</i>

185
00:10:27,827 --> 00:10:31,698
<i>At his age, it's impossible for</i>
<i>Gin to change his character.</i>

186
00:10:32,832 --> 00:10:33,867
<i>But Kagura.</i>

187
00:10:33,867 --> 00:10:35,335
<i>There's still time for you.</i>

188
00:10:36,236 --> 00:10:38,271
<i>It's time to grow up!</i>
<i>Kagura!</i>

189
00:10:41,808 --> 00:10:43,309
Dammit!
What have you done?

190
00:10:46,713 --> 00:10:47,580
What?

191
00:11:03,496 --> 00:11:04,764
Oh, good boy.

192
00:11:04,764 --> 00:11:07,467
Good boy, well done, Sadaharu!

193
00:11:07,634 --> 00:11:09,269
Let's go home and apologize.

194
00:11:09,269 --> 00:11:11,004
Although, I'm still a little bit mad.

195
00:11:11,771 --> 00:11:15,341
However, this sword looks best
on Gintoki's belt, after all.

196
00:11:17,544 --> 00:11:18,878
<i>I'm home, everyone!</i>

197
00:11:19,379 --> 00:11:20,446
Ouch!

198
00:11:20,446 --> 00:11:21,948
Oh my goodness!

199
00:11:22,081 --> 00:11:24,984
I can't believe I'm being mugged
by a bunch of samurais!

200
00:11:25,251 --> 00:11:26,719
Today's my date with Jennifer.

201
00:11:26,719 --> 00:11:27,820
What rotten luck.

202
00:11:27,820 --> 00:11:28,788
Shit!

203
00:11:29,055 --> 00:11:30,490
Jennifer is not coming.

204
00:11:30,490 --> 00:11:32,458
And you are going to
die here, Michael.

205
00:11:32,625 --> 00:11:33,359
Hey.

206
00:11:33,359 --> 00:11:34,594
What're you doing here, Marilyn?

207
00:11:34,594 --> 00:11:36,563
Nobody said anything about this.

208
00:11:36,930 --> 00:11:39,599
Listen here, I heard you
called me "Frankenstein"

209
00:11:39,599 --> 00:11:41,301
when you went out drinking
the other day!

210
00:11:41,301 --> 00:11:43,469
Even though I told you the
only thing I've had done

211
00:11:43,469 --> 00:11:45,204
was my nose, you bastard!

212
00:11:45,471 --> 00:11:47,707
I'm going to take this
legendary sword "Star Destroyer,"

213
00:11:47,707 --> 00:11:49,075
and tear apart your blonde ass

214
00:11:49,075 --> 00:11:50,810
and make sure you're never
able to walk again!!

215
00:11:51,010 --> 00:11:53,513
<i>This sword was fashioned from</i>
<i>a ten thousand year‐old tree</i>

216
00:11:53,513 --> 00:11:56,382
<i>made of Adamantine that</i>
<i>grows on a distant planet.</i>

217
00:11:56,883 --> 00:11:59,485
<i>This amazing wooden sword</i>
<i>can cut through rock,</i>

218
00:11:59,485 --> 00:12:02,055
meteors, and even
your stupid muscles.

219
00:12:02,055 --> 00:12:03,156
That's right!

220
00:12:03,156 --> 00:12:03,890
<i>Buy now!</i>

221
00:12:03,890 --> 00:12:06,893
<i>And as part of our special offer,</i>
<i>we'll even engrave the hilt!</i>

222
00:12:06,893 --> 00:12:07,927
<i>‐Only 12 payments!</i>
‐Yes.

223
00:12:07,927 --> 00:12:08,928
‐Just this much
‐Yes!

224
00:12:08,928 --> 00:12:09,963
‐per month. Yes!
‐Yup.

225
00:12:09,963 --> 00:12:11,631
<i>‐And you too,</i>
‐Engrave it with "Lake Toya" as always.

226
00:12:11,631 --> 00:12:12,999
<i>‐can become an invincible samurai!</i>
‐That's "Lake Toya Resort."

227
00:12:12,999 --> 00:12:13,933
‐Isn't that awesome?!
‐No...

228
00:12:13,933 --> 00:12:16,636
I think I'll just stick with the
usual "Lake Toya" again.

229
00:12:16,936 --> 00:12:19,372
Gintoki, what are you doing
on the phone?

230
00:12:20,106 --> 00:12:21,674
Oh, listen to this, Kagura.

231
00:12:21,808 --> 00:12:23,710
I got lucky at the casino, you see...

232
00:12:23,710 --> 00:12:26,679
and the other day, I spilled curry
on my wooden sword,

233
00:12:26,679 --> 00:12:29,916
and it smelled so bad,
I splurged on a brand new one.

234
00:12:30,583 --> 00:12:32,418
What?
A wooden sword, like that one?

235
00:12:32,418 --> 00:12:33,553
That's right!

236
00:12:33,553 --> 00:12:34,988
But don't tell Shinpachi about it,

237
00:12:35,121 --> 00:12:36,823
because I want to keep it
mysterious, you know.

238
00:12:36,823 --> 00:12:39,158
I'll buy you something so you
keep quiet, what would you like?

239
00:12:39,559 --> 00:12:40,293
